import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.scatter(data['US_Gross'], data['Worldwide_Gross'])
    plt.xlabel('US_Gross')
    plt.ylabel('Worldwide_Gross')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of US_Gross and Worldwide_Gross?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
